{
  "stem": "9503.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, there are some.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] One dates back to-- a lot of-- wait a minute.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Let me say that a lot of my experiencing this period as a child has to do with being disillusioned in  humanity.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] being really shook by things that went on sometimes between people, Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It is like you expect it from the Germans, but I had some childlike idea that all the Jews would band together against all the Germans, which was not the case.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was a lot of nationalism.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Dutch Jews and the German Jews didn't get along.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Dutch Jews, the Czechoslovakian Jews, the German Jews didn't get along in-- in-- in Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And somehow or other, that, in a way, I think, disappointed me more than the danger from without, which I had grown up with that, to expect that.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The other came as a shock time and time again.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I remember that I had a-- a little friend.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, let-- let's call it a boyfriend.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You know, when you're 11 years old, it's nothing, you know, serious.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was a male little friend.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he came to Theresienstadt on the same transport that we did with his brother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "His parents had long disappeared.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He already lived in an orphanage in-- in Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And at first, his brother was put on transport around the time that my father was, and then he was.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I remember that I brought him to the train.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I wasn't allowed to-- I-- I-- I went with him as far as was allowed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "When my father went, my mother didn't want me there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
